kicanvas.js — vendored third-party asset
========================================

Project:   KiCanvas
Author:    Alethea Katherine Flowers (theacodes)
Upstream:  https://github.com/theacodes/kicanvas
License:   MIT
Source:    https://kicanvas.org/kicanvas/kicanvas.js
Fetched:   2026-07-15 (upstream Last-Modified 2026-04-28)

KiCanvas is an interactive, browser-based viewer for KiCad schematics and PCBs.
Stockroom embeds it self-hosted (no CDN, no network in the render path) to render
a registered project's .kicad_sch / .kicad_pcb in-app. The bundle self-registers the
<kicanvas-embed> and <kicanvas-source> custom elements. Project files are fed to it as
INLINE <kicanvas-source> text (the bytes are fetched with the per-launch bearer token
and inlined), so the viewer never issues its own unauthenticated fetch.

LOCAL MODIFICATION (Stockroom): the upstream bundle injects, at import time, a
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/..."> to the Google Fonts CDN
(Material Symbols Outlined + Nunito). That would beacon to Google on every viewer open,
break the offline-first / strict-CSP posture, and contradict the "no network in the render
path" promise above. The single href has been repointed to the self-hosted
"/vendor/kicanvas-fonts.css" (this directory), which @font-face's the woff2 files under
vendor/fonts/ (downloaded from the same Google Fonts request, rewritten to local paths).
This is the ONLY change from upstream; the bundle is otherwise the upstream esbuild output.

